title: Rural Municipality of Fillmore No. 96
text:
The Rural Municipality of Fillmore No. 96 (<a href="Canada%202016%20Census">2016 population</a>: ) is a <a href="List%20of%20rural%20municipalities%20in%20Saskatchewan">rural municipality</a> (RM) in the <a href="Provinces%20and%20territories%20of%20Canada">Canadian province</a> of <a href="Saskatchewan">Saskatchewan</a> within <a href="Division%20No.%202%2C%20Saskatchewan">Census Division No. 2</a> and <a href="SARM%20Division%20No.%201">Division No. 1</a>. It is located in the south-east portion of the province along <a href="Saskatchewan%20Highway%2033">Highway 33</a>.
History.
The RM of Fillmore No. 96 incorporated as a rural municipality on December 13, 1909. It was previously Local Improvement District No. 6–E–2.
Geography.
Communities and localities.
The following <a href="List%20of%20municipalities%20in%20Saskatchewan%23Urban%20municipalities">urban municipalities</a> are surrounded by the RM.
The following unincorporated communities are within the RM.
Osage Wildlife Refuge.
Osage Wildlife Refuge is a wildlife <a href="List%20of%20protected%20areas%20of%20Saskatchewan%23Other%20Sites%20with%20Provincial%20Protection">conservation area</a> in the RM of Fillmore, about 3 miles south-east of Osage along Highway 33. It is on the south side of the highway at 49°56′0″N, 103°33′2″W.
Demographics.
In the <a href="2016%20Canadian%20Census">2016 Census of Population</a> conducted by <a href="Statistics%20Canada">Statistics Canada</a>, the RM of Fillmore No. 96 recorded a population of living in of its total private dwellings, a change from its 2011 population of . With a land area of , it had a population density of in 2016.
In the <a href="2011%20Canadian%20Census">2011 Census of Population</a>, the RM of Fillmore No. 96 recorded a population of , a change from its 2006 population of . With a land area of , it had a population density of in 2011.
Government.
The RM of Fillmore No. 96 is governed by an elected municipal council and an appointed administrator that meets on the second Wednesday of every month. The <a href="Reeve%20%28Canada%29">reeve</a> of the RM is Russell Leguee while its administrator is Vernna Wiggins. The RM's office is located in Fillmore.
